**************
The probability \( P(Y_7 < 27.3) \) is determined using the order statistics of eight independent observations from a continuous distribution with the 70th percentile \( \pi_{0.7} = 27.3 \). For a continuous distribution, \( P(X < 27.3) = P(X \leq 27.3) = 0.7 \).

The event \( Y_7 < 27.3 \) is equivalent to at least seven observations being less than 27.3. Let \( K \) be the number of observations less than 27.3, so \( K \sim \text{Binomial}(n=8, p=0.7) \). Then:
\[
P(Y_7 < 27.3) = P(K \geq 7) = P(K=7) + P(K=8).
\]

Calculate the probabilities:
- \( P(K=7) = \binom{8}{7} (0.7)^7 (0.3)^1 = 8 \times (0.7)^7 \times 0.3 \)
- \( P(K=8) = \binom{8}{8} (0.7)^8 (0.3)^0 = 1 \times (0.7)^8 \times 1 = (0.7)^8 \)

Compute the values:
- \( (0.7)^7 = 0.0823543 \)
- \( P(K=7) = 8 \times 0.0823543 \times 0.3 = 0.19765032 \)
- \( (0.7)^8 = 0.05764801 \)
- \( P(K=8) = 0.05764801 \)

Sum the probabilities:
\[
P(K \geq 7) = 0.19765032 + 0.05764801 = 0.25529833
\]

Rounding to three significant figures, the result is 0.255. The answer is a probability and has no unit.

