The difference \(D = X - Y\) is normally distributed. The mean of \(D\) is \(\mu_D = \mu_X - \mu_Y = 800 - 850 = -50\) hours. The variance of \(D\) is \(\sigma_D^2 = \sigma_X^2 + \sigma_Y^2 = 14400 + 2500 = 16900\), so the standard deviation is \(\sigma_D = \sqrt{16900} = 130\) hours. Thus, \(D \sim N(-50, 16900)\).

