- 19% have low blood pressure (L).
- 17% have an irregular heartbeat (I).
- Of those with an irregular heartbeat, 35% have high blood pressure, so the percentage with both irregular heartbeat and high blood pressure is 17% × 35% = 5.95%.
- The percentage with normal blood pressure (N) is 100% - 16% - 19% = 65%.
- Of those with normal blood pressure, 11% have an irregular heartbeat, so the percentage with both irregular heartbeat and normal blood pressure is 65% × 11% = 7.15%.

The total percentage with irregular heartbeat is the sum of those with irregular heartbeat and high, normal, or low blood pressure:
- 17% = 5.95% + 7.15% + percentage with irregular heartbeat and low blood pressure.
- Thus, percentage with irregular heartbeat and low blood pressure = 17% - 5.95% - 7.15% = 3.90%.

The percentage with low blood pressure is the sum of those with low blood pressure and irregular heartbeat plus those with low blood pressure and regular heartbeat:
- 19% = 3.90% + percentage with low blood pressure and regular heartbeat.
- Thus, percentage with low blood pressure and regular heartbeat = 19% - 3.90% = 15.10%.

