Solution: The probability \( P(Y_7 < 27.3) \) is determined using the order statistics of eight independent observations from a continuous distribution with the 70th percentile \( \pi_{0.7} = 27.3 \). For a continuous distribution, \( P(X < 27.3) = P(X \leq 27.3) = 0.7 \).

