Problem:  If $P(A)=0.8, P(B)=0.5$, and $P(A \cup B)=0.9$. What is $P(A \cap B)$? The unit of the answer should be  .
Solution: The probability of the intersection of events A and B, \( P(A \cap B) \), is calculated using the formula for the union of two events:  
\[ P(A \cup B) = P(A) + P(B) - P(A \cap B) \]  
Rearranging for \( P(A \cap B) \):  
\[ P(A \cap B) = P(A) + P(B) - P(A \cup B) \]  
Substituting the given values:  
