\[
E_{\text{pos}} = -13.6 \times \frac{\mu}{m_e} = -13.6 \times \frac{1}{2} = -6.8  \text{eV}
\]

The value \(-6.8  \text{eV}\) is rounded to three significant figures, consistent with the given hydrogen ground-state energy. The summary explicitly states the final answer as \(-6.8\).

